@endnode

@node fileformat "The amazingly good ALS PREFERENCES FILEFORMAT!  Hurrah!"
Before I start wibbling on about this, I'd better warn you that it's in a
bit of a mess.  This is simply because I've added new features, and just
tagged them on the end.  Anyway, you should be able to work out whats going
on.  The file is just a simple ascii text file, and should be saved as
ENV:ALS/Library.prefs

Note: This description isn't necessarily correct!

End of game message (broken mower)
Open on a custom screen (not tested much)
Lawnmower name 1
Status of mower 1 (0=broken, 1=working)
Lawnmower name 2
Status of mower 2
Lawnmower 3
Status of mower 3
Lawnmower 4
Status of mower 4
Lawnmower 5
Status of mower 5
Lawnmower 6
Status of mower 6
End of game message 1
End of game message 2
End of game message 3
End of game message 4
End of game message 5
End of game message 6
End of game message 7
End of game message 8
End of game message 9
Speed of scrolly messages (higher=slower)
Background (0=day, 1=night, 2=random)
X position of window
Y position of window
Width of window
Height of window
Lawnmower name 7 (hidden mower)
Status of mower 7 (0=off, 1=broken, 2=working)
Activate message 10 (0=off, 1=on)
End of game message 10 (needs activating above)
@endnode

